Luna-RS
========================================

This project is a Rust rewrite of Luna.

DUAL LICENSING
--------------

This repository contains code under multiple licenses:

1. Files derived from the upstream Luna C implementation are licensed under
   the Mozilla Public License v1.1 (MPL-1.1). See LICENSE.MPL for full text.

   Currently, this includes:
   - src/core/des.rs
   - src/core/compression.rs
   - src/core/xml.rs

2. New code written for Luna-RS (CLI, application logic, and other new
   implementations) is licensed under the MIT License. See LICENSE.MIT
   for full text.

ATTRIBUTION
-----------

Original Luna Project:
  - Original C implementation of Luna
  - TI-Nspire document wrapping/encryption logic (luna.c)
  - Licensed under Mozilla Public License v1.1

Luna-RS Contributors:
  - Rust rewrite implementation
  - Architecture and module design
  - Licensed under MIT License (new code)

DEPENDENCIES
------------

This project uses various open-source dependencies. See Cargo.toml for a
complete list. Notable dependencies include:

  - des: Cryptography library (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
  - cipher: Cryptography traits (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
  - flate2: Compression library (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
  - zip: ZIP archive handling (MIT)
  - crc32fast: CRC32 implementation (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
  - thiserror: Error derive macros (MIT OR Apache-2.0)

Please refer to each dependency's license for their specific terms.

If you distribute binaries, you may need to include copies of relevant
third-party license texts (and any required NOTICE files). Tools like
`cargo-about` can help generate a bundled third-party notices file.
